modules.description: Handles cookie-based session management and persistent storage for HTTP servers, using CoHTTP, Webmachine, Async, and Lwt. Operates on session identifiers, cookie headers, and backend storage structures like in-memory maps or file-based stores. Enables secure user authentication by tracking session state across requests, allowing restricted access to routes until a session is established.

Provides session management operations over Redis, including generating keys with custom or default expiration, retrieving session values with their expiry, updating session data, and clearing stored sessions. Works with strings as keys and values, and integer-based periods for expiration. Used to handle user sessions in web applications, storing and retrieving temporary data with controlled lifetimes.
